Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of error-correcting codes and decoding algorithms for compute-and-forward relaying, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also focuses on the performance analysis of LDPC codes over two-way relay channels, which is a subfield of networked information systems (cs.NI). The use of spatially coupled LDPC codes is also discussed, which is a topic in signal processing and communications (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the comparison of the CAF scheme with the MAC separation decoding scheme, which is a topic in computer communications (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses the mutual information rate and rate achievability, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
